const questions = [
    [{"Explanation":"Dedicated Hosts provide a customer with full control over physical servers, allowing compliance with specific security and licensing requirements. This option is ideal for regulated industries needing hardware-level isolation and visibility.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Dedicated Hosts","Savings Plans","On Demand","Spot Instances"],"CorrectAnswer":"Dedicated Hosts","QuestionText":"A financial services company needs to run sensitive applications that handle confidential customer data and require compliance with industry regulations. They need complete control over the physical server, including instance placement and resource allocation. Which pricing option should they choose?","SK":"DOMAIN#Billing&Pricing#ID#97"},{"Explanation":"Spot Instances let you use unused EC2 capacity at discounts of up to 90% compared to On-Demand pricing. They are ideal for fault-tolerant, flexible workloads such as batch processing or data analysis that can handle interruptions.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Reserved Instances","Savings Plans","On Demand","Spot Instances"],"CorrectAnswer":"Spot Instances","QuestionText":"A startup is running a batch processing workload that can tolerate occasional interruptions, and they want to reduce costs by taking advantage of unused Amazon EC2 capacity. Which pricing option would offer them the most savings?","SK":"DOMAIN#Billing&Pricing#ID#98"},{"Explanation":"On-Demand pricing is ideal for new workloads with unpredictable usage. It allows you to pay only for the compute you use, without long-term commitments, providing flexibility as usage patterns stabilize.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Reserved Instances","Savings Plans","On Demand","Spot Instances"],"CorrectAnswer":"On Demand","QuestionText":"A customer is building a new application and is unsure of their usage patterns but expects to grow and stabilize usage over time. They want to start without a long-term commitment. Which pricing option should they use?","SK":"DOMAIN#Billing&Pricing#ID#99"},{"Explanation":"When selecting a Region, consider compliance requirements and proximity to users to meet regulations and minimize latency.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Any regulatory compliance standards the agency requires","Proximity to users","Number of files stored","Personal preference of the CIO","How recently the Region was constructed"],"CorrectAnswer":["Any regulatory compliance standards the agency requires","Proximity to users"],"QuestionText":"Which factors are MOST important to consider when selecting an AWS Region? (Select TWO.)","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#0"},{"Explanation":"This advantage allows companies to pay only for the resources they consume.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Trade fixed expense for variable expense","Benefit from massive economies of scale","Stop guessing capacity","Increase speed and agility"],"CorrectAnswer":"Trade fixed expense for variable expense","QuestionText":"A company wants to migrate its on-premises workloads to AWS to transition from upfront capital expenditures (CapEx) to variable operational expenditures (OpEx). Which advantage of cloud computing does this represent?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#001"},{"Explanation":"The Reliability pillar encompasses the ability of a system to recover from infrastructure or service disruptions.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Operational Excellence","Reliability","Performance Efficiency","Security"],"CorrectAnswer":"Reliability","QuestionText":"Which pillar of the AWS Well-Architected Framework focuses on the ability of a workload to perform its intended function correctly and consistently?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#002"},{"Explanation":"Elasticity is the ability to acquire resources as you need them and release them when they are no longer needed.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Global reach","High availability","Elasticity","Economy of scale"],"CorrectAnswer":"Elasticity","QuestionText":"A startup is launching a new application and is unsure of the initial traffic patterns. Which cloud benefit allows them to adjust resource levels automatically as traffic grows?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#003"},{"Explanation":"Customers are responsible for 'Security in the Cloud,' including OS patching.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Physical security of data centers","Patching the underlying guest operating system on EC2","Maintaining the virtualization software","Disposal of physical storage disks"],"CorrectAnswer":"Patching the underlying guest operating system on EC2","QuestionText":"Under the AWS Shared Responsibility Model, which of the following is a responsibility of the customer?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#004"},{"Explanation":"Designing for failure involves creating architectures that remain functional even when specific components fail.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Design for failure","Scale vertically","Implement loose coupling","Build monolithic architectures"],"CorrectAnswer":"Design for failure","QuestionText":"Which design principle of the AWS Well-Architected Framework suggests that systems should be designed to withstand the failure of individual components?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#005"},{"Explanation":"Edge locations are used by Amazon CloudFront to cache content closer to end-users.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Availability Zones","AWS Regions","Edge Locations","VPC Peering"],"CorrectAnswer":"Edge Locations","QuestionText":"A company wants to deploy its application to users globally with very low latency. Which AWS infrastructure component should they use to cache content closer to users?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#006"},{"Explanation":"Agility refers to the speed at which IT resources are available to developers.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["The ability to deploy resources globally in minutes","The reduction in costs due to AWS purchasing power","Increased speed to develop and ship new applications","Automatically scaling resources based on CPU usage"],"CorrectAnswer":"Increased speed to develop and ship new applications","QuestionText":"Which of the following describes the 'Agility' benefit of cloud computing?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#007"},{"Explanation":"AZs are physically separated locations designed to be isolated from failures in other AZs.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["To provide data residency within a specific country","To provide high availability and fault tolerance","To reduce the cost of data transfer between regions","To connect on-premises data centers to the cloud"],"CorrectAnswer":"To provide high availability and fault tolerance","QuestionText":"What is the primary purpose of having multiple Availability Zones (AZs) within an AWS Region?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#008"},{"Explanation":"The Platform Perspective helps stakeholders optimize their cloud infrastructure.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Governance Perspective","Operations Perspective","Business Perspective","Platform Perspective"],"CorrectAnswer":"Platform Perspective","QuestionText":"Which AWS Cloud Adoption Framework (AWS CAF) perspective focuses on transforming the IT infrastructure and managing IT services?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#009"},{"Explanation":"The AWS Pricing Calculator allows users to estimate and compare costs.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Pricing Calculator","AWS Budgets","AWS Cost Explorer","AWS Trusted Advisor"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Pricing Calculator","QuestionText":"A company is comparing the cost of running a data center on-premises versus AWS. Which tool should they use to estimate the cost savings?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#010"},{"Explanation":"Operational Excellence includes automating tasks to reduce human error.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Cost Optimization","Sustainability","Operational Excellence","Performance Efficiency"],"CorrectAnswer":"Operational Excellence","QuestionText":"In the Well-Architected Framework, which pillar emphasizes the use of serverless architectures to reduce management overhead?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#011"},{"Explanation":"Economies of scale occur when AWS achieves lower costs by aggregating usage.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS passing savings from high-volume hardware purchases to customers","The ability to scale EC2 instances","Using multiple regions","Provisioning a database in minutes"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS passing savings from high-volume hardware purchases to customers","QuestionText":"Which of the following is an example of 'Economies of Scale' in AWS?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#012"},{"Explanation":"Distributing a workload across multiple AZs protects against the failure of a single facility.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Deploy across multiple Edge Locations","Deploy across multiple Availability Zones","Deploy in a single VPC","Use AWS Direct Connect"],"CorrectAnswer":"Deploy across multiple Availability Zones","QuestionText":"A developer needs to ensure that an application remains available even if a single data center fails. Which strategy should they use?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#013"},{"Explanation":"Users can adjust capacity dynamically to match usage instead of predicting peaks.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Must always over-provision","Scale resources automatically based on actual demand","Pay a flat monthly fee","AWS predicts future patterns"],"CorrectAnswer":"Scale resources automatically based on actual demand","QuestionText":"What does the 'Stop Guessing Capacity' benefit of cloud computing mean?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#014"},{"Explanation":"The customer is responsible for configuring the networking security settings.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS","The Customer","Third-party","Both"],"CorrectAnswer":"The Customer","QuestionText":"Under the AWS Shared Responsibility Model, who is responsible for the configuration of Security Groups and Network ACLs?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#015"},{"Explanation":"The Sustainability pillar focuses on energy consumption and efficiency.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Sustainability","Cost Optimization","Operational Excellence","Reliability"],"CorrectAnswer":"Sustainability","QuestionText":"Which Well-Architected pillar focuses on minimizing the environmental impact of running cloud workloads?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#016"},{"Explanation":"A hybrid deployment connects cloud-based and non-cloud resources.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Public Cloud","Private Cloud","Hybrid Deployment","SaaS"],"CorrectAnswer":"Hybrid Deployment","QuestionText":"Which cloud deployment model involves a company running some resources on-premises and some in the AWS Cloud?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#017"},{"Explanation":"AWS's global infrastructure allows for rapid deployment across the world.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Pay in local currency","Deploying applications to multiple regions in minutes","Lowering costs with Reserved Instances","Running any OS on EC2"],"CorrectAnswer":"Deploying applications to multiple regions in minutes","QuestionText":"Which of the following is a benefit of the 'Global Reach' of AWS?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#018"},{"Explanation":"Automation allows developers to spin up environments instantly.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Free technical support","Providing Infrastructure as Code services","Requiring long-term contracts","Eliminating testing"],"CorrectAnswer":"Providing Infrastructure as Code services","QuestionText":"How does AWS help customers reduce their 'Time to Market'?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#019"},{"Explanation":"CloudFormation allows you to treat infrastructure as code.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon CloudWatch","AWS CloudFormation","AWS Config","Amazon Inspector"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS CloudFormation","QuestionText":"Which AWS service helps customers adhere to 'Operational Excellence' by automating resource deployment through templates?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#020"},{"Explanation":"High Availability ensures a system is always accessible.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Operating continuously without intervention","Scaling infinitely","Lowest cost","Unlimited data storage"],"CorrectAnswer":"Operating continuously without intervention","QuestionText":"What is the AWS definition of 'High Availability'?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#021"},{"Explanation":"AWS is responsible for the 'Security of the Cloud' (hardware and facilities).","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Client-side encryption","Physical security of the hardware","IAM","Firewall configuration"],"CorrectAnswer":"Physical security of the hardware","QuestionText":"Under the Shared Responsibility Model, AWS is responsible for which of the following?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#022"},{"Explanation":"The Business Perspective helps align migration with business goals.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Business Perspective","Governance Perspective","Security Perspective","People Perspective"],"CorrectAnswer":"Business Perspective","QuestionText":"Which perspective of the AWS Cloud Adoption Framework (AWS CAF) focuses on ensuring IT investments support business outcomes?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#023"},{"Explanation":"Loose coupling ensures that if one component fails, others continue to function.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Connecting all components into a single file","Components interacting without being dependent on each other","Using only one AZ","Manually adjusting capacity"],"CorrectAnswer":"Components interacting without being dependent on each other","QuestionText":"Which of the following best describes 'Loose Coupling' in cloud architecture?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#024"},{"Explanation":"AWS Artifact provides on-demand access to AWS compliance reports.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Artifact","AWS Shield","AWS WAF","AWS Trusted Advisor"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Artifact","QuestionText":"A company wants to identify which AWS service will help them manage their compliance reports. Which service should they use?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#025"},{"Explanation":"AWS secures the infrastructure running cloud services, while customers secure data, configurations, and access inside the cloud.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS manages security of the cloud; customers manage security in the cloud","Customers manage all aspects of security and compliance","AWS is responsible for customer data security only","Both AWS and customers share identical responsibilities for all security tasks"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS manages security of the cloud; customers manage security in the cloud","QuestionText":"What is the AWS shared responsibility model?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#1"},{"Explanation":"The client-server model works by having the client send a request to the server, which processes the request and sends back a response. The barista preparing and serving coffee represents this exchange.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["The customer takes a cup of coffee from a self-serve station without informing the barista. This describes how a client and server do not interact.","The barista proactively prepares a coffee and brings it to the customer without being asked. This describes how the client does not need to submit a request to the server.","The customer makes their own coffee using the coffee shop equipment without interacting with the barista. This describes how the client does not require the server.","The customer goes to the barista and places an order for a coffee. The barista prepares the coffee and hands it back to the customer. This describes how the client places the request, and the server responds."],"CorrectAnswer":"The customer goes to the barista and places an order for a coffee. The barista prepares the coffee and hands it back to the customer. This describes how the client places the request, and the server responds.","QuestionText":"In our coffee shop example, a barista and customer were used to represent the client-server model. Which scenario BEST describes how the client-server model works in this analogy?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#10"},{"Explanation":"When selecting a Region, organizations should evaluate compliance requirements and proximity to end users. These factors affect data residency laws and latency performance.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Regulatory compliance requirements in that location","Proximity to your users for lower latency","The number of Amazon EC2 instances available","Your organization’s default AWS account settings","Whether the Region uses renewable energy sources"],"CorrectAnswer":["Regulatory compliance requirements in that location","Proximity to your users for lower latency"],"QuestionText":"Which of the following are key factors to consider when choosing an AWS Region? (Select TWO.)","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#107"},{"Explanation":"AWS Regions are global geographic areas. Each Region includes multiple Availability Zones, which are isolated data centers designed for high availability and fault tolerance.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["A Region is a data center, while an Availability Zone is a single physical server.","A Region is a geographic location containing multiple Availability Zones, and each Availability Zone is an isolated data center or group of data centers.","An Availability Zone spans multiple Regions across the world.","Regions and Availability Zones refer to the same thing in AWS."],"CorrectAnswer":"A Region is a geographic location containing multiple Availability Zones, and each Availability Zone is an isolated data center or group of data centers.","QuestionText":"What is the difference between AWS Regions and Availability Zones?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#108"},{"Explanation":"Edge locations are part of AWS’s global content delivery network (CDN) and cache data closer to users to reduce latency and improve download speeds.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Global Accelerator","Amazon CloudFront Edge Location","AWS Direct Connect Gateway","Amazon Route 53 Resolver"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon CloudFront Edge Location","QuestionText":"Which AWS component caches content closer to users to improve performance and reduce latency?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#109"},{"Explanation":"A hybrid cloud deployment combines on-premises resources with cloud-based infrastructure. It allows sensitive data to remain on-premises for compliance while using the cloud for scalable and flexible workloads.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["On-premises deployment","Public cloud deployment","Hybrid deployment","Data-compliance deployment"],"CorrectAnswer":"Hybrid deployment","QuestionText":"You work for a local charity organization. Your organization has sensitive data that must remain within your country for compliance reasons. However, you also need a solution that can scale quickly to handle seasonal spikes in demand. You decide to keep on-premises resources for compliance and use cloud-based resources for dynamic scaling. Which type of cloud deployment does this situation describe?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#11"},{"Explanation":"AWS CloudFormation lets you define infrastructure as code through reusable templates that automatically provision and configure AWS resources.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Elastic Beanstalk","AWS CloudFormation","AWS OpsWorks","AWS Systems Manager"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS CloudFormation","QuestionText":"Which AWS service allows you to model and automate the setup of AWS infrastructure using templates?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#110"},{"Explanation":"Using multiple Availability Zones increases application reliability and uptime by spreading workloads across physically separate data centers.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Improved fault tolerance and high availability","Reduced AWS pricing","Automatic compliance with all international data regulations","Increased application latency","Redundancy in case of infrastructure failure"],"CorrectAnswer":["Improved fault tolerance and high availability","Redundancy in case of infrastructure failure"],"QuestionText":"What are the main advantages of deploying AWS resources across multiple Availability Zones? (Select TWO.)","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#111"},{"Explanation":"Elasticity in AWS allows resources to automatically adjust capacity in response to traffic or demand changes, optimizing cost and performance.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Elasticity","High availability","Durability","Compliance"],"CorrectAnswer":"Elasticity","QuestionText":"Which benefit of AWS infrastructure allows businesses to automatically scale resources up or down as demand changes?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#112"},{"Explanation":"AWS resources can be managed via the Management Console, CLI, SDKs, or IaC tools like CloudFormation—not through the AWS Marketplace.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Management Console","AWS Command Line Interface (CLI)","AWS Software Development Kits (SDKs)","Amazon Marketplace"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon Marketplace","QuestionText":"Which method is NOT used to interact with AWS resources?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#113"},{"Explanation":"Infrastructure as Code (IaC) allows developers to define and automate AWS resource creation using templates—improving consistency and reducing manual effort.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["A system that automatically repairs hardware failures in AWS data centers","The practice of defining and managing infrastructure using code templates instead of manual configuration","A pricing model that bills based on infrastructure usage","The method AWS uses to control physical access to its facilities"],"CorrectAnswer":"The practice of defining and managing infrastructure using code templates instead of manual configuration","QuestionText":"What is Infrastructure as Code (IaC)?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#114"},{"Explanation":"AWS SDKs provide APIs for multiple programming languages, enabling developers to directly interact with AWS services programmatically.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Software Development Kit (SDK)","AWS Command Line Interface (CLI)","AWS Management Console","AWS Systems Manager"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Software Development Kit (SDK)","QuestionText":"Which tool would you use to interact with AWS through programming languages such as Python or JavaScript?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#115"},{"Explanation":"When choosing an AWS Region, agencies must consider regulatory compliance and proximity to users. These determine whether data handling meets legal requirements and ensures low-latency access for end users.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Any regulatory compliance standards the agency requires","Proximity to users","Number of files stored","Personal preference of the chief information officer","How recently the Region was constructed"],"CorrectAnswer":["Any regulatory compliance standards the agency requires","Proximity to users"],"QuestionText":"A cloud engineer for a government agency is tasked with selecting an AWS Region to deploy the agency's resources. Which factors are MOST important to consider when selecting a Region? (Select TWO.)","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#116"},{"Explanation":"AWS Global Infrastructure consists of Regions (geographic groupings of data centers), Availability Zones (isolated data center clusters within Regions), and Edge Locations (local caching endpoints for low-latency content delivery).","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Edge location","AWS Region","Availability Zone"],"CorrectAnswer":{"Edge location":"Locations that cache content to deliver data, video, and applications to users with lower latency","AWS Region":"A physical location around the world where AWS operates multiple data centers","Availability Zone":"Separate, distinct locations with one or more data centers that are engineered to be isolated from failures in other areas"},"QuestionText":"Match each AWS Global Infrastructure element with its correct definition.","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#117"},{"Explanation":"AWS Regions provide global coverage, Availability Zones ensure redundancy and high availability within Regions, and Edge Locations deliver content with low latency to users.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Regions host data centers; Availability Zones distribute workloads within Regions; Edge Locations cache content closer to end users.","Edge Locations host the main AWS data centers; Regions handle caching for faster delivery; Availability Zones connect them.","Regions are for testing, Availability Zones for production, and Edge Locations for backup only.","Edge Locations and Availability Zones are the same thing in AWS Global Infrastructure."],"CorrectAnswer":"Regions host data centers; Availability Zones distribute workloads within Regions; Edge Locations cache content closer to end users.","QuestionText":"Which statement BEST describes how AWS Regions, Availability Zones, and Edge Locations work together?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#118"},{"Explanation":"AWS CloudFormation enables developers to model and provision infrastructure through code templates, ensuring consistent and repeatable deployments for complex architectures like EC2, Load Balancing, and Auto Scaling.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["CloudFormation would not be useful in this scenario because it only supports simple infrastructure setups.","CloudFormation would be ideal because it supports infrastructure as code (IaC), enabling consistent, repeatable deployments across different environments.","CloudFormation should be used only for setting up static websites, not for complex applications.","CloudFormation is too complicated and would slow down the deployment process."],"CorrectAnswer":"CloudFormation would be ideal because it supports infrastructure as code (IaC), enabling consistent, repeatable deployments across different environments.","QuestionText":"A rapidly growing tech startup company is planning to launch a new web application that will require a complex infrastructure setup, including multiple Amazon EC2 instances, Elastic Load Balancing, and Auto Scaling groups. The application must be deployed consistently across different environments. Would AWS CloudFormation be a good solution for managing the company's infrastructure?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#119"},{"Explanation":"AWS removes the need to estimate capacity requirements. You can scale resources up or down automatically to match demand, ensuring performance without overprovisioning or underutilization.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Stop spending money to run and maintain data centers.","Stop guessing capacity.","Trade upfront expense for variable expense.","Go global in minutes."],"CorrectAnswer":"Stop guessing capacity.","QuestionText":"A retail business plans to launch a new line of clothing, but they are struggling with accurately predicting how much server capacity they will need to support the launch. Which benefit of the AWS Cloud is most relevant to this situation?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#12"},{"Explanation":"AWS achieves high availability through its global infrastructure of Regions and Availability Zones. If one data center fails, workloads can automatically shift to another, minimizing downtime and maintaining service continuity.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS stores all of your website’s data in a single AWS storage bucket to centralize data management.","AWS has many customer support options to make sure the answers to your questions are highly available on its website.","AWS provides multiple data centers across different geographic regions so your website can remain operational even if one location faces issues.","AWS offers a single, highly secure data center that can handle all your traffic, which makes sure that your website is available."],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS provides multiple data centers across different geographic regions so your website can remain operational even if one location faces issues.","QuestionText":"You just joined a tech start-up, and the business is growing rapidly. Your new company decides that they need to design a resilient and scalable infrastructure on AWS to handle increased traffic and help ensure high availability. Which statement BEST describes the AWS Global Infrastructure benefit of high availability?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#13"},{"Explanation":"AWS Global Infrastructure provides multiple Regions and Availability Zones that allow applications to remain operational even during component failures. This design enhances both fault tolerance and high availability for global workloads.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Fault tolerance","Cost savings","Ease of use","High availability","Compliance with regulatory standards"],"CorrectAnswer":["Fault tolerance","High availability"],"QuestionText":"Your company is planning to launch a new web application that will serve users around the world. To help ensure the application performs well and remains reliable, the IT team plans to use AWS for its vast global infrastructure. What BEST describes the benefits of AWS Global Infrastructure related to this situation? (Select TWO.)","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#14"},{"Explanation":"One of the core advantages of cloud computing is eliminating the need to manage physical data centers. AWS handles infrastructure operations, allowing organizations to reduce costs and focus on innovation.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Benefit from massive economies of scale","Stop guessing capacity","Stop spending money running and maintaining data centers","Increase speed and agility"],"CorrectAnswer":"Stop spending money running and maintaining data centers","QuestionText":"A large enterprise is looking to lower operational costs. They are hoping to reduce the operational overhead associated with managing their own physical infrastructure. Which choice BEST describes which advantage of the cloud this enterprise can benefit from?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#15"},{"Explanation":"An AWS Region is a distinct geographic area with multiple Availability Zones. Each Availability Zone is an isolated data center or group of data centers within that Region, enabling fault tolerance and high availability.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["An Availability Zone spans multiple physical locations across Regions, and Regions are located across the world.","A Region is a geographical location that contains three or more Availability Zones. An Availability Zone is a distinct location within a Region that contains one or more discrete data centers.","An Availability Zone is a geographical location that contains three or more Regions. A Region is a distinct location within an Availability Zone that contains one or more discrete data centers.","A Region is a single data center, and an Availability Zone consists of multiple data centers."],"CorrectAnswer":"A Region is a geographical location that contains three or more Availability Zones. An Availability Zone is a distinct location within a Region that contains one or more discrete data centers.","QuestionText":"You work for a sports apparel company that is expanding its operations to global customers. The company wants to deploy resources to multiple AWS locations to achieve high availability. You are tasked with explaining the basics of AWS Global Infrastructure to your chief operating officer (COO). The COO needs help understanding the difference between AWS Regions and Availability Zones. Which statement BEST describes the difference between AWS Regions and Availability Zones?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#16"},{"Explanation":"A hybrid deployment allows an organization to maintain on-premises infrastructure while integrating specific applications or workloads with the AWS Cloud. This provides flexibility and control while benefiting from cloud scalability.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Cloud","Compliance","Hybrid","On-premises"],"CorrectAnswer":"Hybrid","QuestionText":"A government agency wants to maintain complete control over its IT infrastructure, but plans to use AWS Cloud services for specific applications. Which deployment type is BEST for this situation?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#17"},{"Explanation":"Cloud computing provides on-demand access to IT resources via the internet using a pay-as-you-go model. This reduces large fixed capital expenses and allows companies to scale costs based on actual usage.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Cloud computing is basically just using someone else's server to host your website, and it does not offer any sort of significant cost advantages over traditional hosting solutions.","Cloud computing is a model for delivering IT resources over the internet. Businesses can rent services on a pay-as-you-go basis, which can help reduce fixed costs and allow for more flexible budgeting.","Cloud computing reduces the need for additional hardware but still involves significant fixed monthly fees.","Cloud computing involves purchasing dedicated servers and setting up a private data center. This model often comes with fixed costs related to hardware and maintenance."],"CorrectAnswer":"Cloud computing is a model for delivering IT resources over the internet. Businesses can rent services on a pay-as-you-go basis, which can help reduce fixed costs and allow for more flexible budgeting.","QuestionText":"A small business is considering migrating their IT infrastructure to the cloud. The finance team has a meeting with the IT department to discuss the costs associated with this transition. During the meeting, the finance manager says they like the idea of the reliability that comes with the cloud, but they are worried about the fixed costs. Which statement accurately defines the cloud computing model and addresses the finance manager's concern?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#18"},{"Explanation":"Scalability and elasticity allow AWS resources to automatically adjust to changing workloads. This ensures performance during peak demand while optimizing costs during low activity periods.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["The ability to manually adjust resources based on peak usage","The ability to grow and shrink resources dynamically based on real-time demand","The ability to create fixed resources that never change in size","The ability to permanently increase resource capacity for long-term growth"],"CorrectAnswer":"The ability to grow and shrink resources dynamically based on real-time demand","QuestionText":"What is the primary benefit of scalability and elasticity in AWS?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#19"},{"Explanation":"Pay-as-you-go pricing allows scaling up or down as needed, reducing costs compared to traditional fixed infrastructure.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["You pay only for the services you use without long-term contracts or upfront costs","You must commit to a fixed monthly price for predictable billing","You pay in advance for all resources to guarantee capacity","You pay the same regardless of how much you use"],"CorrectAnswer":"You pay only for the services you use without long-term contracts or upfront costs","QuestionText":"Which statement BEST describes the benefit of the AWS Cloud’s pay-as-you-go pricing model?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#2"},{"Explanation":"AWS enables businesses to scale resources up or down automatically in response to demand. This elasticity ensures performance during peak times while reducing costs when usage drops.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["By providing fixed resources that are always available","By allowing businesses to provision resources that automatically scale based on demand","By requiring businesses to purchase excess resources in advance to handle peak demand","By offering resources that are always running, regardless of demand"],"CorrectAnswer":"By allowing businesses to provision resources that automatically scale based on demand","QuestionText":"How does AWS make sure that a business can meet fluctuating demand without over-provisioning resources?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#20"},{"Explanation":"The AWS Pricing Calculator lets you model architecture and estimate costs before deployment.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Budgets","AWS Pricing Calculator","AWS Cost Explorer","AWS Trusted Advisor"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Pricing Calculator","QuestionText":"Which AWS tool helps estimate monthly costs for a solution before deploying it?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#3"},{"Explanation":"AWS global infrastructure includes multiple Regions (geographic areas), Availability Zones (isolated data centers), and Edge Locations (for content delivery).","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["A collection of physical servers that run customer applications","A network of Regions, Availability Zones, and Edge Locations","Data centers managed by third-party hosting providers","A global CDN that stores cached data only"],"CorrectAnswer":"A network of Regions, Availability Zones, and Edge Locations","QuestionText":"Which of the following BEST describes the AWS global infrastructure?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#4"},{"Explanation":"CloudTrail records account activity and API calls for governance, compliance, and auditing.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS CloudTrail","Amazon CloudWatch","AWS Config","AWS Trusted Advisor"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS CloudTrail","QuestionText":"Which AWS service provides visibility into user activity and API usage across your AWS account?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#5"},{"Explanation":"The cloud enables on-demand scaling and flexible pricing, allowing organizations to match resources to actual demand.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Eliminating all operational costs","Reducing the need for network connectivity","Gaining elasticity and scalability while paying only for usage","Avoiding security responsibilities"],"CorrectAnswer":"Gaining elasticity and scalability while paying only for usage","QuestionText":"What is the primary benefit of migrating workloads to the AWS Cloud?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#6"},{"Explanation":"CloudFormation automates deployment of infrastructure through code templates for consistent environments.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Elastic Beanstalk","AWS CloudFormation","AWS OpsWorks","AWS Systems Manager"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS CloudFormation","QuestionText":"Which AWS service provides a consistent way to deploy and manage infrastructure as code?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#7"},{"Explanation":"AWS Shield provides managed DDoS protection for AWS resources and applications.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Shield","AWS WAF","Amazon Inspector","AWS Artifact"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Shield","QuestionText":"Which AWS service or feature helps protect against Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#8"},{"Explanation":"Each Region has multiple AZs that are physically separated to minimize risk of simultaneous failure.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["They are separate data centers within an AWS Region, designed for high availability and fault tolerance","They are local caching servers for CloudFront","They represent user accounts in AWS","They are used only for AWS government workloads"],"CorrectAnswer":"They are separate data centers within an AWS Region, designed for high availability and fault tolerance","QuestionText":"Which statement BEST describes AWS Availability Zones?","SK":"DOMAIN#CloudConcepts#ID#9"},{"Explanation":"Lambda is a fully managed serverless compute service that executes code in response to events without needing servers.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon EC2","AWS Lambda","Amazon ECS","AWS Batch"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Lambda","QuestionText":"Which AWS compute model allows you to run code without provisioning servers?","SK":"DOMAIN#Compute#ID#100"},{"Explanation":"While AWS manages the Lambda infrastructure, customers are responsible for securing their code and correctly configuring IAM roles and permissions for services the function accesses.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Patching the underlying operating system","Scaling the infrastructure","Managing data access permissions","Managing server availability"],"CorrectAnswer":"Managing data access permissions","QuestionText":"A development team at a fintech startup is building a new customer-facing microservice using AWS Lambda. AWS takes care of the infrastructure, but the team is focused on meeting strict security and compliance requirements. Which task is still the team's responsibility when using Lambda?","SK":"DOMAIN#Compute#ID#101"},{"Explanation":"Lambda workflows consist of functions (code), triggers (events), and runtimes (language environments). AWS handles infrastructure, scaling, and OS management automatically.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Lambda function","Triggers","Server provisioning","Runtimes","Manual scaling configuration","Operating system selection"],"CorrectAnswer":["Lambda function","Triggers","Runtimes"],"QuestionText":"A photography company offers cloud-based photo editing and storage. It uses AWS Lambda to automatically process photos—resizing images, applying filters, and organizing files—every time a client uploads a new image. Which key components are involved in running this automated workflow with Lambda? (Select THREE.)","SK":"DOMAIN#Compute#ID#102"},{"Explanation":"Containers bundle the application and all dependencies into one portable, consistent runtime environment. This ensures the app runs identically across development, testing, and production.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["By providing access to multiple operating systems for compatibility testing","By packaging the application and everything it needs to run into one consistent environment","By automatically scaling the application across multiple cloud providers","By eliminating the need to write configuration files"],"CorrectAnswer":"By packaging the application and everything it needs to run into one consistent environment","QuestionText":"A developer just finished building an application that runs flawlessly on their laptop. However, when the team deploys it in a different environment, it crashes due to missing dependencies. How do containers help solve this problem?","SK":"DOMAIN#Compute#ID#103"},{"Explanation":"Amazon EKS is a managed Kubernetes service; Amazon ECR is for container image storage and management; AWS Fargate runs containers without servers; and Amazon ECS orchestrates containerized workloads on AWS.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon Elastic Kubernetes Service (Amazon EKS)","Amazon Elastic Container Registry (Amazon ECR)","AWS Fargate","Amazon Elastic Container Service (Amazon ECS)"],"CorrectAnswer":{"AWS Fargate":"Serverless compute engine for containers—removes the need to manage servers","Amazon Elastic Container Registry (Amazon ECR)":"Stores, manages, and deploys Open Container Initiative (OCI)-compliant container images","Amazon Elastic Kubernetes Service (Amazon EKS)":"Fully managed Kubernetes service for deploying and scaling containers","Amazon Elastic Container Service (Amazon ECS)":"Scalable container orchestration service for running containers on AWS"},"QuestionText":"Match each AWS container service with its correct definition.","SK":"DOMAIN#Compute#ID#104"},{"Explanation":"Amazon Lightsail provides easy-to-use VPSs with predictable pricing, AWS Outposts extends AWS infrastructure on-premises, AWS Batch runs large-scale batch jobs efficiently, and Elastic Beanstalk simplifies web app deployment and scaling.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon Lightsail","AWS Outposts","AWS Batch","AWS Elastic Beanstalk"],"CorrectAnswer":{"AWS Batch":"A fully managed service for batch computing workloads","Amazon Lightsail":"A simplified service with virtual private servers (VPSs), storage, and networking","AWS Elastic Beanstalk":"A managed service for deploying and scaling web applications","AWS Outposts":"A hybrid cloud service extending AWS to on-premises environments"},"QuestionText":"Match each AWS service with the correct description.","SK":"DOMAIN#Compute#ID#105"},{"Explanation":"AWS Outposts extends AWS infrastructure, services, and APIs to on-premises environments. It provides a consistent hybrid experience, allowing organizations to run AWS services locally while meeting compliance and low-latency requirements.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Elastic Beanstalk","Amazon Lightsail","AWS Batch","AWS Outposts"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Outposts","QuestionText":"A financial company must run workloads on premises because of strict compliance requirements, but it wants to use AWS services and tools consistently across environments. Which service meets their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Compute#ID#106"},{"Explanation":"Networking in AWS refers to the communication and data exchange between interconnected systems, instances, and services.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["System that translates readable domain names to IP addresses","Logically isolated section of the AWS Cloud where you can launch AWS resources in a virtual network that you define","Physically isolated data centers or set of data centers within an AWS Region","Interconnected devices that can exchange data and resources"],"CorrectAnswer":"Interconnected devices that can exchange data and resources","QuestionText":"What is networking in the AWS Cloud?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#41"},{"Explanation":"CloudFront is a global content delivery network (CDN) that caches data at AWS edge locations to reduce latency for users.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon Route 53","Amazon CloudFront","AWS Direct Connect","AWS Global Accelerator"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon CloudFront","QuestionText":"Which AWS service helps deliver content globally with low latency?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#42"},{"Explanation":"Route 53 provides domain registration, DNS routing, and health checking for resources inside and outside AWS.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon CloudFront","Amazon Route 53","AWS Direct Connect","AWS Global Accelerator"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon Route 53","QuestionText":"Which AWS service can be used to register and manage domain names?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#43"},{"Explanation":"Amazon CloudFront caches and distributes video and static content globally to ensure low latency and high performance.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon CloudFront","Amazon Route 53","AWS Direct Connect","AWS Global Accelerator"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon CloudFront","QuestionText":"A financial company needs to deliver media-rich training videos to consultants worldwide with minimal latency. Which AWS service should they use?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#44"},{"Explanation":"Route 53 provides both DNS management and domain registration, allowing routing to on-premises or AWS resources.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Global Accelerator","Amazon CloudFront","AWS Direct Connect","Amazon Route 53"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon Route 53","QuestionText":"A media company wants a service to manage domain registrations and route internet traffic to resources both inside and outside AWS. Which AWS service fits this need?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#45"},{"Explanation":"Direct Connect establishes a private, dedicated connection between an on-premises network and AWS for consistent performance.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS VPN","AWS PrivateLink","AWS Direct Connect","AWS Global Accelerator"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Direct Connect","QuestionText":"Which AWS service provides a dedicated network connection from an on-premises data center to AWS?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#46"},{"Explanation":"AWS Client VPN is a managed client-based VPN solution that allows secure access for users from any location.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Client VPN","AWS Site-to-Site VPN","AWS PrivateLink","AWS Direct Connect"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Client VPN","QuestionText":"Which AWS service enables remote employees to securely connect to AWS and on-premises networks?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#47"},{"Explanation":"Private subnets in a VPC allow hosting of internal resources that are not directly accessible from the internet.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Internet Gateway","Private Subnet","VPC Peering","Route Table"],"CorrectAnswer":"Private Subnet","QuestionText":"Which AWS feature allows creation of a private subnet to isolate resources from internet access?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#48"},{"Explanation":"Network ACLs operate at the subnet level and support both allow and deny rules for controlling traffic.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Security Groups","Network ACLs","Route Tables","PrivateLink"],"CorrectAnswer":"Network ACLs","QuestionText":"A company wants broad control of traffic in and out of a subnet using both allow and deny rules. What should they use?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#49"},{"Explanation":"Direct Connect provides a secure and private connection, ideal for organizations with compliance and bandwidth requirements.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Direct Connect","AWS VPN","AWS PrivateLink","Amazon CloudFront"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Direct Connect","QuestionText":"A healthcare company needs a private, dedicated connection to AWS for compliance reasons. Which AWS service should they use?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#50"},{"Explanation":"Global Accelerator routes traffic to optimal endpoints using AWS’s global network, improving availability and latency.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Direct Connect","Amazon CloudFront","AWS Global Accelerator","Amazon Route 53"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Global Accelerator","QuestionText":"A company wants to route user requests based on health checks and latency to improve application performance. Which service should they use?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#51"},{"Explanation":"DNS converts friendly domain names (like example.com) into IP addresses so devices can connect over networks.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Translates human-readable names into IP addresses","Caches website content for faster delivery","Encrypts internet connections","Monitors application traffic"],"CorrectAnswer":"Translates human-readable names into IP addresses","QuestionText":"What is the primary function of a Domain Name System (DNS)?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#52"},{"Explanation":"Site-to-Site VPN establishes encrypted IPsec tunnels between customer sites and AWS over the internet.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Client VPN","AWS Site-to-Site VPN","AWS Direct Connect","AWS Global Accelerator"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Site-to-Site VPN","QuestionText":"Which AWS component provides secure connections between on-premises networks and AWS VPCs over the internet?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#53"},{"Explanation":"Security groups act as virtual firewalls for EC2 instances, controlling inbound and outbound traffic.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Network ACLs","Security Groups","Route Tables","Private Subnets"],"CorrectAnswer":"Security Groups","QuestionText":"Which network component allows traffic control at the instance level within a VPC?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#54"},{"Explanation":"Network ACLs operate at the subnet level, offering broader traffic control with both allow and deny rules.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Security Groups","Network ACLs","Route Tables","VPC Peering"],"CorrectAnswer":"Network ACLs","QuestionText":"Which AWS feature allows control of inbound and outbound traffic at the subnet level?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#55"},{"Explanation":"Direct Connect delivers private, high-bandwidth connections between on-premises environments and AWS.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Direct Connect","AWS VPN","AWS PrivateLink","AWS Global Accelerator"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Direct Connect","QuestionText":"A customer needs a dedicated connection to AWS for high bandwidth workloads. Which service provides this?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#56"},{"Explanation":"Client VPN provides managed, secure access for remote employees using client software with authentication support.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Client VPN","AWS Site-to-Site VPN","AWS Direct Connect","AWS PrivateLink"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Client VPN","QuestionText":"A company merged with another and wants to quickly provide secure remote access for global employees to AWS resources. Which solution fits best?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#57"},{"Explanation":"A Virtual Private Gateway is used to establish VPN connections between on-premises networks and a VPC.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Internet Gateway","Virtual Private Gateway","Subnet","Route Table"],"CorrectAnswer":"Virtual Private Gateway","QuestionText":"Which AWS component enables a secure private connection between an on-premises data center and a VPC?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#58"},{"Explanation":"Global Accelerator routes traffic through AWS’s global network to healthy endpoints for better performance and availability.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Global Accelerator","Amazon Route 53","Amazon CloudFront","AWS Direct Connect"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Global Accelerator","QuestionText":"Which AWS service helps route traffic globally and improve performance by using static IP addresses and endpoint health?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#59"},{"Explanation":"Subnets in a VPC allow you to organize AWS resources logically. Public subnets can host internet-facing resources, while private subnets keep sensitive systems isolated. They help segment and manage resources efficiently, but do not themselves provide high availability or computing capacity.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Can be used to share public resources","Can be used to organize your resources","Can be used to provide high availability because they consist of one or more discrete data centers","Can provide a centralized interface for accessing and managing various AWS resources and services","Can be used to isolate resources and keep them private","Can be used as an on-demand and scalable computing capacity in the AWS Cloud"],"CorrectAnswer":["Can be used to share public resources","Can be used to organize your resources","Can be used to isolate resources and keep them private"],"QuestionText":"What are the uses of a subnet in an Amazon VPC? (Select THREE.)","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#60"},{"Explanation":"A virtual private gateway allows secure communication between on-premises networks and AWS over a VPN connection. Using a private subnet keeps the resources isolated from public internet access while maintaining secure connectivity.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["An internet gateway with a public subnet holding the resources in the Amazon VPC","A virtual private gateway with a VPN connection and a private subnet in the Amazon VPC","An internet gateway with an Amazon VPC and no subnets","An internet gateway with an Amazon VPC and a public subnet"],"CorrectAnswer":"A virtual private gateway with a VPN connection and a private subnet in the Amazon VPC","QuestionText":"A company is setting up their Amazon VPC. They need to connect their corporate data center through the internet with a secure connection. They also want to make sure the resources are isolated from the public. Which solution would BEST meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#61"},{"Explanation":"AWS Direct Connect provides a dedicated, high-bandwidth, private network connection between on-premises data centers and AWS. It’s ideal for large-scale data transfers and ongoing hybrid cloud architectures.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Client VPN","AWS Site-to-Site VPN","AWS Direct Connect link to their on-premises network and the AWS Cloud","AWS PrivateLink to their on-premises data center"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Direct Connect link to their on-premises network and the AWS Cloud","QuestionText":"A company is conducting a large-scale migration of their on-premises data center with their data warehouse and data backup. They need a solution that will meet the large amount of bandwidth requirements during migration. The solution will also be used for their ongoing data transfers after the move because they will retain part of their on-premises data center for a hybrid cloud solution. Which AWS solution would best meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#62"},{"Explanation":"A virtual private gateway enables secure VPN connections between an on-premises network and a VPC. It allows only encrypted, approved network traffic to access private subnets, ensuring protection and isolation.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Internet gateway","Virtual private gateway","AWS Transit Gateway","Amazon API Gateway"],"CorrectAnswer":"Virtual private gateway","QuestionText":"A company is choosing the type of gateway for their network. They need to connect their corporate data center with their private subnet in their Amazon VPC. Their gateway needs to allow only protected internet traffic to enter the VPC and allow connections only from approved networks. Which type of gateway would BEST meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#63"},{"Explanation":"Security groups act as stateful firewalls at the instance level, allowing fine-grained control over inbound and outbound traffic based on application needs. They are ideal for managing traffic rules per EC2 instance.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Change all the subnets to private subnets to avoid accessing from the public internet.","Set up security groups for the EC2 instances based on the application requirements.","Set up network ACLs for the EC2 instances based on the application requirements.","Set up a public subnet with strong passwords that meet the customer's requirements."],"CorrectAnswer":"Set up security groups for the EC2 instances based on the application requirements.","QuestionText":"A retail customer is setting up their application in the AWS Cloud. The application requires a lot of control in defining traffic rules for the individual Amazon EC2 instances in their public subnet. Which solution would BEST meet the requirements for securing the resources?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#64"},{"Explanation":"Network ACLs operate at the subnet level and use stateless packet filtering, meaning they evaluate each packet individually without remembering previous connections.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Private subnet","Network access control list (network ACL)","Amazon VPC","Security groups"],"CorrectAnswer":"Network access control list (network ACL)","QuestionText":"Which network component performs stateless packet filtering?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#65"},{"Explanation":"Amazon CloudFront is a content delivery network (CDN) that caches and delivers data globally with low latency, making it ideal for distributing media-rich training content efficiently.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon VPC","Amazon Route 53","Amazon CloudFront","AWS Global Accelerator"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon CloudFront","QuestionText":"An enterprise customer with a worldwide sales force is looking to deliver their large library of sales training content. They want to make sure their sales force can access the media-rich training content with low latency and reduced costs. Which AWS service would BEST fit the customer's need?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#66"},{"Explanation":"Amazon Route 53 is a scalable DNS service that allows customers to register, manage, and route traffic for multiple domain names in one place.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon VPC","Amazon Route 53","Amazon CloudFront","AWS Global Accelerator"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon Route 53","QuestionText":"After years of working with different domain registration companies, a media company is looking for a solution to manage all their existing domain names. They also want to register new domain names. Ideally, they would like to manage all their domain names in a single service. Which AWS service would BEST fit the customer's need?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#67"},{"Explanation":"AWS Direct Connect provides a dedicated, private connection between an organization’s data center and AWS, reducing latency, increasing bandwidth, and ensuring compliance for sensitive data transfers like healthcare workloads.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Standard internet connection from the client to an internet gateway in the VPC in the AWS Cloud","VPN connection from their corporate data center to the AWS Cloud","VPN connection from their corporate data center to a virtual private gateway to their Amazon VPC","AWS Direct Connect connection from their corporate data center to a virtual private gateway in their VPC in the AWS Cloud"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Direct Connect connection from their corporate data center to a virtual private gateway in their VPC in the AWS Cloud","QuestionText":"A healthcare company is looking to create a dedicated network connection to AWS. They would use this connection for their heavy payloads of data being sent over the internet to AWS. They also have compliance requirements due to the sensitive nature of their patient data. Which type of connection to the AWS Cloud would BEST meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#68"},{"Explanation":"Under the AWS Shared Responsibility Model, AWS secures the infrastructure that runs cloud services, while customers are responsible for securing their data, applications, and network configurations — including security groups and network ACLs.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Securing access to the AWS data centers and facilities that run AWS Cloud services","Securing the software that runs the AWS Cloud services","Securing the hardware that runs the AWS Cloud services","Securing network traffic with the subnets and resources with Network access control lists (network ACLs) and security groups"],"CorrectAnswer":"Securing network traffic with the subnets and resources with Network access control lists (network ACLs) and security groups","QuestionText":"A customer is creating their application resources in their virtual private cloud (VPC) subnets. They want to secure their resources in the cloud, specifically the networking traffic protection tasks. Which component is the customer responsible for, based on the shared responsibility model?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#69"},{"Explanation":"In AWS, networking is based on Amazon VPC — a logically isolated section of the cloud where you can define your own IP address range, subnets, and route tables to securely manage and connect your resources.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Interconnected devices that can exchange data and resources","Physically isolated data centers or set of data centers within an AWS Region","Logically isolated section of the AWS Cloud where you can launch AWS resources in a virtual network that you define","System that translates readable domain names to IP addresses"],"CorrectAnswer":"Logically isolated section of the AWS Cloud where you can launch AWS resources in a virtual network that you define","QuestionText":"What is networking in the AWS Cloud?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#70"},{"Explanation":"AWS Client VPN is a fully managed, elastic VPN service that enables secure connections for remote workers to AWS and on-premises networks. It supports advanced authentication and automatically scales with user demand.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Client VPN","AWS Direct Connect","AWS PrivateLink","AWS Site-to-Site VPN"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Client VPN","QuestionText":"An enterprise customer just merged with another company and needs a way to quickly scale and provide a way for the new worldwide sales force to access their AWS resources. They want a fully managed service with advanced authentication for their new remote workers. Which solution would BEST meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#71"},{"Explanation":"Amazon Route 53 is a scalable Domain Name System (DNS) web service that allows users to register domain names and route traffic to AWS or external resources with high availability and low latency.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Global Accelerator","Amazon CloudFront","Amazon Route 53","AWS Direct Connect"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon Route 53","QuestionText":"A media company needs a service to manage their domain registrations with different providers. They will also be using the service to route internet traffic to their resources hosted both in the AWS Cloud and elsewhere. Which AWS solution would BEST meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#72"},{"Explanation":"AWS Site-to-Site VPN creates a secure and encrypted connection between on-premises networks and AWS resources over the internet, offering a cost-effective solution for securely connecting multiple sites without requiring additional bandwidth.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Site-to-Site VPN","AWS Client VPN","AWS Direct Connect","AWS PrivateLink"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Site-to-Site VPN","QuestionText":"A customer is exploring solutions to establish secure, encrypted connections between their on-premises networks at their data centers and branch offices. They are looking for the MOST cost-effective way to connect their office sites to other sites and their AWS services. They are not looking to increase the amount of bandwidth. Which solution would BEST meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#73"},{"Explanation":"AWS Direct Connect provides a dedicated, private connection between on-premises networks and AWS, offering increased bandwidth, lower latency, and a more consistent network experience than internet-based connections.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Direct Connect","Internet gateway","Virtual private gateway","Amazon CloudFront"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Direct Connect","QuestionText":"A customer wants a way to establish a dedicated connection from their on-premises network to an Amazon VPC. They need a solution that provides a more consistent network experience with increased bandwidth. Which type of connection to the AWS Cloud would BEST meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#74"},{"Explanation":"Security groups act as virtual firewalls at the instance level in a VPC, allowing you to define multiple inbound and outbound rules to control traffic for specific Amazon EC2 instances.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Set up security groups for the Amazon EC2 instances based on the application requirements.","Change the public subnet to a private subnet to avoid public internet access.","Set up a virtual private gateway based on the application requirements.","Set up network access control lists (network ACLs) for the Amazon EC2 instances based on the application requirements."],"CorrectAnswer":"Set up security groups for the Amazon EC2 instances based on the application requirements.","QuestionText":"A retail customer is hosting their application in an Amazon VPC and wants to configure traffic rules for the Amazon EC2 instances running in a public subnet. The application requires multiple rules to be defined at the instance level. Which solution or feature would meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#75"},{"Explanation":"A virtual private gateway enables secure, encrypted communication between an on-premises data center and an Amazon VPC through a VPN connection, making it ideal for hybrid cloud architectures.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Internet gateway","Subnet","Route table","Virtual private gateway"],"CorrectAnswer":"Virtual private gateway","QuestionText":"A company wants to establish a secure, private connection between their on-premises data center and their Amazon VPC to create a hybrid cloud architecture. Which component should they use to help ensure a secure connection?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#76"},{"Explanation":"AWS Global Accelerator uses the AWS global network to route traffic to the nearest healthy endpoint based on user location, configured policies, and endpoint health—improving application performance and availability.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Global Accelerator","Amazon CloudFront","Amazon Route 53","AWS Direct Connect"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Global Accelerator","QuestionText":"A customer is exploring edge networking services to improve application availability, performance, and security. They need a solution for traffic routing when something goes wrong in one of their application's locations. Specifically, it takes into account the endpoint health, user location, and policies. Which AWS solution would BEST meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#77"},{"Explanation":"A private subnet in an Amazon VPC isolates resources from direct access to the internet, allowing only internal communication or access through secure connections such as VPN or NAT gateways.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["A private subnet","Either a public subnet or a private subnet would work","A public subnet","An Availability Zone instead of a subnet"],"CorrectAnswer":"A private subnet","QuestionText":"A customer is creating an Amazon VPC for their application. They want to create a private segment in the Amazon VPC so that resources launched can be isolated from users on the internet. Which network component would BEST meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#78"},{"Explanation":"Availability Zones are isolated locations within an AWS Region that are designed to prevent failures from affecting other zones. Deploying resources across multiple Availability Zones increases fault tolerance and application availability.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["It filters inbound and outbound traffic to EC2 instances in a VPC.","It enhances application availability and fault tolerance by allowing resources to be deployed across multiple zones.","It allows you to create a subsection of a virtual private cloud (VPC) where you can isolate resources and control access.","It provisions a logically isolated section of the AWS Cloud where you can launch AWS resources in a virtual network that you define."],"CorrectAnswer":"It enhances application availability and fault tolerance by allowing resources to be deployed across multiple zones.","QuestionText":"What is the primary function of an Availability Zone in the AWS Cloud?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#79"},{"Explanation":"A domain name service (DNS) translates domain names like www.example.com into IP addresses that computers use to identify each other on the network. AWS provides Route 53 as a scalable DNS service for this purpose.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["It translates human-readable domain names to machine readable IP addresses.","It filters inbound and outbound traffic to Amazon EC2 instances in a virtual private cloud (VPC).","It provisions a logically isolated section of the AWS Cloud where you can launch AWS resources in a virtual network that you define.","It allows you to create a subsection of a virtual private cloud (VPC) where you can isolate resources and control access."],"CorrectAnswer":"It translates human-readable domain names to machine readable IP addresses.","QuestionText":"What is the primary function of a domain name service (DNS)?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#80"},{"Explanation":"Network access control lists (network ACLs) operate at the subnet level and support both allow and deny rules. They provide stateless, broad control over inbound and outbound traffic for subnets, unlike security groups which operate at the instance level and only support allow rules.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Change the public subnet to a private subnet to avoid public internet access.","Set up a virtual private gateway based on the application requirements.","Use security groups.","Use network access control lists (network ACLs)."],"CorrectAnswer":"Use network access control lists (network ACLs).","QuestionText":"A customer is moving their application to an Amazon VPC and wants to set up traffic control at the subnet level. They need broad control of traffic in and out and would like to use both allow and deny type rules. Which solution or feature would meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#81"},{"Explanation":"Amazon CloudFront is a global content delivery network (CDN) that securely delivers static and dynamic content with low latency by caching copies at AWS edge locations around the world. This ensures faster access for users regardless of location.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon Route 53","Amazon CloudFront","AWS Global Accelerator","AWS Direct Connect"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon CloudFront","QuestionText":"A financial customer needs a content delivery solution to deliver required training videos and static content to their financial consultants worldwide. They want to make sure the solution provides low latency. Which AWS solution would BEST meet their needs?","SK":"DOMAIN#Networking&ContentDelivery#ID#82"},{"Explanation":"AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) allows you to manage users, groups, and roles to securely control access to AWS resources.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS IAM","AWS Organizations","AWS Control Tower","AWS Cognito"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS IAM","QuestionText":"Which AWS service enables centralized identity management and access control across AWS accounts and services?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#83"},{"Explanation":"AWS Organizations lets you centrally manage multiple AWS accounts with consolidated billing and service control policies.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS IAM","AWS Organizations","AWS Control Tower","AWS CloudFormation"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Organizations","QuestionText":"Which AWS service enables multi-account governance, allowing consolidated billing and policy management?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#84"},{"Explanation":"Customers are responsible for security 'in' the cloud, such as network configurations and access permissions.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Securing the hardware and facilities that run AWS Cloud services","Securing the software that runs AWS Cloud services","Securing network traffic with subnets, security groups, and access controls","Managing the physical security of AWS data centers"],"CorrectAnswer":"Securing network traffic with subnets, security groups, and access controls","QuestionText":"What is the main responsibility of the customer under the AWS shared responsibility model?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#85"},{"Explanation":"AWS Shield automatically protects applications running on AWS from DDoS attacks at no extra cost.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS WAF","AWS Shield","Amazon Inspector","AWS GuardDuty"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Shield","QuestionText":"Which AWS service provides DDoS protection for web applications?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#86"},{"Explanation":"AWS Web Application Firewall (WAF) protects applications by filtering and monitoring HTTP/S requests.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS GuardDuty","AWS WAF","AWS Shield","AWS CloudTrail"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS WAF","QuestionText":"Which AWS service lets you define fine-grained rules to filter and block web requests based on IP addresses or query strings?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#87"},{"Explanation":"GuardDuty uses machine learning and threat intelligence to detect suspicious activity and potential threats.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon Inspector","AWS Config","AWS GuardDuty","AWS CloudTrail"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS GuardDuty","QuestionText":"Which AWS service continuously monitors for malicious activity and unauthorized behavior in your AWS environment?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#88"},{"Explanation":"CloudTrail tracks and logs AWS account activity, including API usage, for auditing and compliance purposes.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS CloudWatch","AWS Config","AWS CloudTrail","AWS Inspector"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS CloudTrail","QuestionText":"Which AWS service provides a record of all account activity, including API calls and user logins?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#89"},{"Explanation":"Amazon Inspector automatically scans workloads for vulnerabilities and generates detailed findings.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Shield","AWS WAF","Amazon Inspector","AWS Config"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon Inspector","QuestionText":"Which AWS service helps assess applications for vulnerabilities and deviations from security best practices?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#90"},{"Explanation":"AWS Config records configuration changes and evaluates them against compliance rules and best practices.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Config","AWS CloudTrail","AWS CloudWatch","AWS Trusted Advisor"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Config","QuestionText":"Which AWS service helps track configuration changes to AWS resources over time for compliance purposes?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#91"},{"Explanation":"Trusted Advisor offers real-time guidance to optimize performance, reduce costs, and improve security and fault tolerance.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Trusted Advisor","AWS GuardDuty","AWS Security Hub","Amazon Inspector"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Trusted Advisor","QuestionText":"Which AWS service provides real-time security recommendations for improving your AWS environment?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#92"},{"Explanation":"Under the shared responsibility model, AWS manages security *of* the cloud (infrastructure, hardware, etc.), while the customer manages security *in* the cloud — including OS updates, configurations, and patches.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS is responsible for applying security patches to the OS.","Your company is responsible applying security patches to the OS.","Both AWS and the customer apply separate patches.","The OS vendor applies the patches."],"CorrectAnswer":"Your company is responsible applying security patches to the OS.","QuestionText":"You work for a startup company that is developing an application in the cloud. A new security update is available for your operating system (OS), and you are tasked with verifying that the OS is patched accordingly. Which statement BEST describes which party is responsible for applying security patches to the OS that is running in the cloud?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#93"},{"Explanation":"Under the shared responsibility model, AWS handles security *of* the cloud — including physical data centers, hardware, and global infrastructure — while customers are responsible for security *in* the cloud, such as data protection and configurations.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS is responsible for securing the physical infrastructure, and the company can focus on securing their data and applications within the cloud.","The company is fully responsible for securing all physical infrastructure of the cloud, including data centers.","The company shares responsibility with the cloud provider for securing the physical infrastructure.","The company does not have any responsibility when it comes to security in the cloud."],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS is responsible for securing the physical infrastructure, and the company can focus on securing their data and applications within the cloud.","QuestionText":"A finance company is interested in migrating to the cloud. They are curious if they will have enough staff to secure both their office space and the physical infrastructure of their cloud computing resources. Which statement BEST describes the company's responsibility when it comes to securing physical infrastructure of the cloud?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#94"},{"Explanation":"Under the AWS Shared Responsibility Model, customers are responsible for security *in* the cloud — including managing OS patches, application configurations, and encryption of client-side data. AWS is responsible for the underlying infrastructure and physical security.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Updating compute, networking, storage, and database software","Managing operating system (OS) patches","Networking and infrastructure hardware maintenance","Encrypting client-side data","Physical security of data centers"],"CorrectAnswer":["Managing operating system (OS) patches","Encrypting client-side data"],"QuestionText":"You are a cloud architect at a company that has recently migrated its infrastructure to AWS. Your manager has asked you to debrief your team on which responsibilities the customer has when it comes to securing cloud resources. What is the customer's responsibility, based on the AWS Shared Responsibility Model? (Select TWO.)","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#95"},{"Explanation":"Under the shared responsibility model, AWS secures the physical infrastructure and hypervisor, while customers are responsible for managing and securing their own operating systems, configurations, and applications within EC2.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS manages the security of the cloud, and the customer manages the security of the infrastructure.","The customer is responsible for securing the physical hardware of their EC2 instances.","AWS is responsible for managing the operating system, networking, and applications on the customer's EC2 instances.","The customer is responsible for configuring, securing, and managing the operating system, networking, and applications on their EC2 instances."],"CorrectAnswer":"The customer is responsible for configuring, securing, and managing the operating system, networking, and applications on their EC2 instances.","QuestionText":"What is the customer's responsibility when using compute services like Amazon EC2 according to the AWS shared responsibility model?","SK":"DOMAIN#Security&Compliance#ID#96"},{"Explanation":"Amazon EC2 offers resizable compute capacity—virtual machines that you can configure and scale for various workloads.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon EC2","AWS Lambda","Amazon S3","AWS Elastic Beanstalk"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon EC2","QuestionText":"Which AWS service provides virtual servers in the cloud?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#21"},{"Explanation":"Elastic Beanstalk handles deployment, load balancing, and scaling so developers can focus on code rather than servers.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Elastic Beanstalk","AWS CloudFormation","AWS OpsWorks","AWS Lambda"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Elastic Beanstalk","QuestionText":"Which AWS service automatically provisions and scales web applications without requiring you to manage infrastructure?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#22"},{"Explanation":"Lambda executes code in response to events and automatically manages compute resources, enabling serverless computing.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon EC2","AWS Fargate","AWS Lambda","Amazon Lightsail"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Lambda","QuestionText":"Which compute service lets you run code without provisioning or managing servers?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#23"},{"Explanation":"Amazon ECS is a fully managed container orchestration service that runs and scales Docker containers.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon ECS","AWS Batch","Amazon EC2","AWS Elastic Beanstalk"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon ECS","QuestionText":"Which AWS service provides managed containers that can run Docker applications?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#24"},{"Explanation":"Amazon Lightsail provides simplified virtual servers with predictable pricing—ideal for smaller projects or quick setups.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon Lightsail","AWS Batch","Amazon EC2","AWS Elastic Beanstalk"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon Lightsail","QuestionText":"Which AWS service allows you to deploy and manage virtual private servers easily with preconfigured options?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#25"},{"Explanation":"DynamoDB is a fully managed NoSQL database service providing fast, consistent performance and seamless scalability.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon RDS","Amazon DynamoDB","Amazon Redshift","Amazon Aurora"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon DynamoDB","QuestionText":"Which AWS database service is a managed NoSQL database that delivers single-digit millisecond performance?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#26"},{"Explanation":"Amazon RDS simplifies setup, operation, and scaling of relational databases like MySQL, PostgreSQL, and SQL Server.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon RDS","Amazon DynamoDB","Amazon Redshift","Amazon ElastiCache"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon RDS","QuestionText":"Which AWS service provides fully managed relational databases?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#27"},{"Explanation":"CloudWatch collects metrics and logs, and enables alarms for operational visibility and automated responses.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS CloudTrail","Amazon CloudWatch","AWS Config","AWS Trusted Advisor"],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon CloudWatch","QuestionText":"Which AWS service helps developers monitor applications and infrastructure performance using metrics and alarms?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#28"},{"Explanation":"CloudFormation defines infrastructure as code to provision AWS resources consistently and repeatedly.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS OpsWorks","AWS CloudFormation","AWS Elastic Beanstalk","AWS Systems Manager"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS CloudFormation","QuestionText":"Which AWS service automates infrastructure deployment using reusable templates?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#29"},{"Explanation":"AWS Batch efficiently runs hundreds or thousands of batch computing jobs by dynamically provisioning resources.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["AWS Batch","AWS Lambda","AWS Fargate","AWS CloudFormation"],"CorrectAnswer":"AWS Batch","QuestionText":"Which AWS service can be used for running batch computing workloads at scale?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#30"},{"Explanation":"EC2 instance store is physically attached to the host and offers extremely low latency and high I/O performance. It is ideal for temporary storage that does not need to persist after instance termination.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["EC2 instance store provides high I/O performance for temporary storage needs.","EC2 instance store reduces overall storage costs by offering the cheapest per-gigabyte storage option in AWS.","EC2 instance store provides a persistent storage solution that survives instance failures.","EC2 instance store allows storage to be conveniently shared between multiple EC2 instances simultaneously."],"CorrectAnswer":"EC2 instance store provides high I/O performance for temporary storage needs.","QuestionText":"A developer is building an application that processes large amounts of data and requires high I/O performance. After processing the data for an operation, the results are displayed to the user and do not need to be retained long-term. Unfortunately, the application's current storage solution is experiencing performance bottlenecks during peak processing times. How could implementing an EC2 instance store improve the performance of the application?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#31"},{"Explanation":"Amazon Elastic Block Store (EBS) provides persistent block-level storage for EC2 instances with high availability and durability by automatically replicating data within the same Availability Zone.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon EBS allows sharing volumes across multiple AWS Regions without any latency impact.","Amazon EBS automatically scales volume capacity without requiring any volume modifications.","Amazon EBS provides unlimited input/output operations per second (IOPS) for all volume types, regardless of size.","Amazon EBS provides high availability and durability by automatically replicating volumes within the same Availability Zone."],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon EBS provides high availability and durability by automatically replicating volumes within the same Availability Zone.","QuestionText":"AnyCompany Finance is designing an application that requires consistent and low-latency access to financial data. They're looking for a storage solution that provides persistent block storage. Why would Amazon EBS be suitable to store data in this scenario?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#32"},{"Explanation":"Amazon EBS volumes are persistent block storage devices that exist independently from EC2 instances. Even if an instance fails or is terminated, the data on the EBS volume remains intact until the volume itself is deleted.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["EBS automatically synchronizes data with Amazon S3 every 5 minutes, ensuring that if an EC2 instance crashes, all data can be immediately restored from the S3 backup.","Amazon EBS caches all data in memory for instant recovery when instances are restarted.","Amazon EBS volumes exist independently from the instance and persist even after the instance is terminated.","Amazon EBS automatically backs up all data to Amazon S3 every hour to help ensure persistence."],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon EBS volumes exist independently from the instance and persist even after the instance is terminated.","QuestionText":"AnyCompany Software is migrating their on-premises application architecture to AWS. They are particularly concerned about data persistence because in their current environment, they have experienced data loss when virtual machines (VMs) crashed. They want to understand how Amazon Elastic Block Store (Amazon EBS) can help address their data persistence requirements when they move their workloads to Amazon EC2 instances. How does Amazon EBS solve the data persistence issue described in this scenario?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#33"},{"Explanation":"EBS snapshots allow you to back up the state of an EBS volume and quickly create new volumes from those snapshots. This enables fast and consistent replication of production environments for testing or staging.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["EBS snapshots enable rapid creation of new volumes from existing data, so you can quickly deploy identical test environments that mirror production.","EBS snapshots automatically optimize the performance of your EBS volumes by defragmenting data during the snapshot process.","EBS snapshots reduce your storage costs by compressing all data on your EBS volumes by up to 90 percent.","EBS snapshots automatically migrate your data to different AWS Regions for improved global access speeds."],"CorrectAnswer":"EBS snapshots enable rapid creation of new volumes from existing data, so you can quickly deploy identical test environments that mirror production.","QuestionText":"AnyCompany Commerce operates an online trading platform experiencing rapid growth. Their development team frequently needs to create test environments that mirror production for testing new features, but setting up these environments has become time-consuming and error-prone. What is the most significant benefit of using EBS snapshots in this scenario?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#34"},{"Explanation":"AWS Data Lifecycle Manager (DLM) allows you to automate the creation, retention, and deletion of EBS snapshots and AMIs, ensuring compliance while reducing manual management and cost overhead.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Providing real-time monitoring of EBS volume performance metrics","Encrypting sensitive patient data stored on EBS volumes","Automating the creation, retention, and deletion of EBS snapshots and EBS backed Amazon Machine Images (AMIs) according to a schedule","Migrating patient data from on-premises storage to AWS Cloud storage"],"CorrectAnswer":"Automating the creation, retention, and deletion of EBS snapshots and EBS backed Amazon Machine Images (AMIs) according to a schedule","QuestionText":"AnyCompany Healthcare manages thousands of EBS volumes containing patient records. They need to ensure that this data is properly backed up, retained according to compliance requirements, and old snapshots are removed to control costs. Which problem does AWS Data Lifecycle Manager primarily solve in this scenario?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#35"},{"Explanation":"Amazon S3 provides object storage for data of any type and scale. It is ideal for storing and distributing mobile app content such as images, videos, and user-generated files, offering high durability and scalability.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Running relational database queries for user authentication","Hosting virtual machines (VMs) to process application logic","Real-time data streaming and message processing","Storing and distributing mobile application content and user-generated media files"],"CorrectAnswer":"Storing and distributing mobile application content and user-generated media files","QuestionText":"AnyCompany Mobile is evaluating cloud storage solutions for their new mobile application. They need a reliable service that can handle various types of data storage requirements as their user base grows. Based on this scenario, what is an aspect of Amazon S3 that they could use in this scenario?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#36"},{"Explanation":"Even if a bucket policy allows public access, S3’s Block Public Access feature can override it. If enabled at the account or bucket level, it prevents any public access until explicitly disabled.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["The images are not properly tagged with public read permissions.","Block public access settings are enabled at the account or bucket level.","They need to enable the website hosting feature to make any Amazon S3 content public.","The S3 bucket must be in the same AWS Region as the users trying to access the content."],"CorrectAnswer":"Block public access settings are enabled at the account or bucket level.","QuestionText":"AnyCompany Marketing has created an Amazon S3 bucket to host images for their new website. The images need to be accessible to anyone visiting the website without authentication. After uploading the images to the bucket, users report they cannot access them, even though the bucket policy is set to allow public access. What is the most likely cause of this access issue?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#37"},{"Explanation":"Amazon S3 is designed for 99.999999999% durability by redundantly storing data across multiple Availability Zones, ensuring protection against data loss for critical media and large file workloads.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Amazon S3 offers 99.999999999 percent (11 nines) of durability for objects stored across multiple Availability Zones. This maintains highly available for their video content and protects it against data loss.","Amazon S3 automatically compresses all stored objects to reduce storage costs by up to 90 percent, making it ideal for large video files.","Amazon S3 limits individual object sizes to 5 GB, requiring companies to split large video files before upload.","Amazon S3 provides built-in video transcoding services that automatically convert videos to different formats when they are uploaded."],"CorrectAnswer":"Amazon S3 offers 99.999999999 percent (11 nines) of durability for objects stored across multiple Availability Zones. This maintains highly available for their video content and protects it against data loss.","QuestionText":"AnyCompany Media is looking for a new cloud storage solution. They distribute large video files to users around the world, and are looking for a service that is highly durable, scalable, and offers various access control mechanisms. Based on this scenario, which Amazon S3 feature would be particularly beneficial?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#38"},{"Explanation":"S3 Lifecycle rules automate the transition of objects between storage classes based on age and access patterns. Using S3 Standard for active data, S3 Standard-IA after 30 days, and S3 Glacier after 90 days optimizes cost while maintaining access when needed.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["Create a lifecycle rule to transition objects to S3 Standard-Infrequent Access (S3 Standard-IA) after 30 days, transition to S3 Glacier after 90 days.","Create a lifecycle rule to immediately transition all objects to S3 Glacier and set up a restore policy.","Create a lifecycle rule to delete all objects after 90 days and rely on database backups.","Create multiple S3 buckets with different storage classes and manually move objects between buckets as they age."],"CorrectAnswer":"Create a lifecycle rule to transition objects to S3 Standard-Infrequent Access (S3 Standard-IA) after 30 days, transition to S3 Glacier after 90 days.","QuestionText":"AnyCompany Business stores a growing amount of customer data in Amazon S3. Their manager is concerned about storage costs and asks IT to implement a solution to move older data to cheaper storage. The data is frequently accessed for the first 30 days, occasionally accessed for the next 60 days, and rarely accessed after 90 days. What should they do in this situation to optimize costs while maintaining appropriate access to the data?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#39"},{"Explanation":"Amazon S3 Lifecycle allows you to define rules that automatically transition objects between storage classes or delete them after a set time. It helps reduce costs by moving data to cheaper tiers as it becomes less frequently accessed.","PK":"EXAM#CLF-C02","Options":["A backup service that creates copies of your S3 objects in different AWS Regions to protect against Regional failures.","A feature that automatically compresses Amazon S3 objects after a certain period to reduce storage costs.","A monitoring system that alerts administrators when Amazon S3 objects have not been accessed for a specified period.","A feature used to define rules to automatically transition objects between different storage classes, or delete them based on age or usage patterns."],"CorrectAnswer":"A feature used to define rules to automatically transition objects between different storage classes, or delete them based on age or usage patterns.","QuestionText":"Which statement BEST describes S3 Lifecycle?","SK":"DOMAIN#Technology#ID#40"}]
];